data.name: groupBox3.ToolTip
data.value: When downloading guide data checking for the lastest changes, download this number of hours. Note: The more hours the longer updates take. Default is 24 hours. Note: With the exception of 24, you guide days must be greater and these hours.

data.name: checkBoxRemapChannelsOnLineupChange.ToolTip
data.value: If this is checked then an attempt will be made to verify the current mapping and if needed re-map existing channels. This can be useful if, for example, two station switch the channels they are broadcast on. Caution: May cause unpredictable results!

data.name: checkBoxAddAnalogChannels.ToolTip
data.value: If this is checked then when new unmapped analog channels are added to Schedules Direct they will be added to MediaPortal using the external input selected for digital. *Not recommended, may cause unpredictable results.

data.name: label18.ToolTip
data.value: This program is not intended for and may not be suitable for children under the age of 17. The program may contain extreme graphic violence, strong profanity, overt explicit sexual dialogue, nudity and/or strong sexual content.

data.name: label17.ToolTip
data.value: Programs issued the TV-14 rating are unsuitable for children under the age of 14 without the guidance of a parent. Many programs that air after 9:00 pm are rated TV-14 with some exceptions. Also, many crime dramas carry the TV-14 rating, such as the Law & Order franchise. Much of Comedy Central's shows such as Mad TV and Mind of Mencia also carry this rating. Many daytime soap operas such as Guiding Light, As The World Turns, and Passions have this rating as well. Certain PG-13 or R rated feature films are rated TV-14 when edited for network or basic cable.

data.name: label16.ToolTip
data.value: This rating signifies that the program is unsuitable for children under the age of 10 without the guidance of a parent. Some game shows and most reality shows are rated TV-PG, including Deal or No Deal, The Power of 10, 1 vs. 100 and American Idol, mainly for their suggestive dialog. The Simpsons, Naruto, Dragon Ball Z (the uncut dub) and Seinfeld maintain a TV-PG rating in every episode. A growing number of programs on Cartoon Network also carry this rating.

data.name: label15.ToolTip
data.value: Programs issued this rating are deemed appropriate for general audiences, however content in these programs are not always specifically intended towards children. Examples of programs issued this rating include The Price Is Right, religious programming, documentaries, Dexter's Laboratory and Full House.

data.name: label14.ToolTip
data.value: These shows may be inapropriate for children under 7 without the guidance of a parant and is more for children who have acquired the developmental skills needed to distinguish the difference between fantasy and reality. These shows may contain comedic violence, fantasy violence (FV), crude or suggestive humor, or may contain scenes that may frighten more impressionable children. It may contain non-cursing language("dang" "Oh My God" and "Oh Snap" and sometimes "sucks") in shows like Ed, Edd n Eddy and Fairly OddParents). Examples of programs issued this rating include Class Of 3000, Aladdin, Time Warp Trio, Foster's Home For Imaginary Friends,Spongebob Squarepants and The Adventures of Jimmy Neutron are issued this rating.

data.name: label11.ToolTip
data.value: The themes and content in programs issued this rating are specifically aimed at a young audience, mainly those ages 2-6. These programs are not expected to frighten or upset young children. Examples of programs issued this rating include The Huggabug Club, Rugrats, Poopster Shep, Go Baby, The New Adventures of Winnie the Pooh, and Thomas and Friends.
